Since you're building a Wikipedia-style semantic GraphRAG, I would make Cell 13 responsible for producing the complete semantic triple (subject, predicate, object) rather than just the predicate. Then Cell 14 only needs to validate, normalize, and store those triples as RDF. This separation makes the pipeline cleaner and easier to debug.
